Here's the pattern for saving/restoring draft text across app lifecycle events in .NET MAUI:

**1. In your `App.xaml.cs` — hook lifecycle events:**

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public static event Action? AppSleep;
    public static event Action? AppResume;

    protected override void OnSleep()
    {
        base.OnSleep();
        AppSleep?.Invoke();
    }

    protected override void OnResume()
    {
        base.OnResume();
        AppResume?.Invoke();
    }
}
```

**2. In your note-taking page (`NotePage.xaml.cs`):**

```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "NoteDraft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        RestoreDraft();
    }

    protected override void OnAppearing()
    {
        base.OnAppearing();
        App.AppSleep += SaveDraft;
        App.AppResume += RestoreDraft;
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        App.AppSleep -= SaveDraft;
        App.AppResume -= RestoreDraft;
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    // Call this when the user explicitly saves/discards
    public void ClearDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }
}
```

**3. In your XAML (`NotePage.xaml`):**

```xml
<Editor x:Name="NoteEditor"
        Placeholder="Start typing your note..." />
```

**Key points:**

- **`Preferences`** is the simplest storage for small text. For larger drafts, use `SecureStorage` or write to `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory`.
- **Subscribe in `OnAppearing` / unsubscribe in `OnDisappearing`** to avoid leaks and ensure only the visible page responds.
- **`OnSleep`** fires when the app is backgrounded — this is your save point.
- **`OnResume`** fires when the app returns — restore here.
- Call `ClearDraft()` when the user explicitly saves or discards the note so stale drafts don't persist.
